Reasoning: The paper deals with the combinatorial characterization of efficient configuration spaces of Euclidean Distance Constraint Systems (EDCS), which includes Linkages and Frameworks. This involves graph theory, forbidden minors, and Cayley parameters. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CG (Computational Geometry), followed by cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.GT (Graph Theory), cs.SD (Systems and Control), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
